      "content": "i see. so for Case B, you're saying the lack of stability might actually lead to a harsher sentence? that seems a bit backwards if we're talking about mitigation. wouldn't those environmental factors—like the poverty and lack of resources you mentioned—be seen as reasons to be *more* lenient or to focus on support instead of punishment? why would those factors make a judge lean towards a harsher sentence?",
